.\" glyph — Emacs-compatible text editor
.Dd 2026-06-15
.Dt GLYPH 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm glyph
.Nd Emacs-compatible text editor
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl R
.Op Fl n
.Op Fl b Ar file
.Op Ar +N
.Op Ar file ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a lightweight, Emacs-compatible text editor, rewritten from mg in Rust.
It supports UTF-8, syntax highlighting, and a miniLisp extension language.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl R
Make all buffers read-only.
.It Fl n
Disable backup files.
.It Fl b Ar file
Batch mode: execute commands from Ar file and exit.
.It Ar + N
Open files starting at line number N.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Nm
supports most standard Emacs keybindings including:
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "M-x" -compact
.It C-n , C-p
Next/previous line
.It C-f , C-b
Forward/backward character
.It C-a , C-e
Beginning/end of line
.It C-v , M-v
Scroll up/down
.It C-s , C-r
Search forward/backward
.It C-space
Set mark
.It C-x C-c
Quit
.It C-x C-f
Find file
.It C-x C-s
Save buffer
.It C-x C-k
Kill buffer
.It C-x C-b
List buffers
.It C-x 2
Split window
.It C-x 0
Delete window
.It C-x o
Other window
.It M-x
Execute extended command
.It M-f , M-b
Forward/backward word
.El
.Sh EXTENSIONS
.Nm
supports a miniLisp scripting language.
Configuration is loaded from
.Pa ~/.config/glyph/config.mg .
.Sh AUTHORS
.Nm
is derived from mg by Han Boetes, which is derived from
MicroEMACS by Dave Conroy, and OpenBSD mg by various contributors.
